            "answer": "<p>Persistent body odor and chronic bad breath that don't respond to external products are often metabolic symptoms — not hygiene problems. Your gut bacteria are responsible for neutralizing trimethylamine (TMA), hydrogen sulfide, and ammonia before they reach your bloodstream. When these bacterial populations deplete, unprocessed volatile compounds are excreted through sweat glands, skin, and breath. Origin restores the specific strains — L. plantarum, L. acidophilus, B. lactis — that handle this internal detoxification.</p>"
