            "answer": "<p>The bacterial strains that metabolize volatile organic compounds — L. plantarum, L. acidophilus — are abundantly present in traditional fermented foods consumed across South Asian, East Asian, African, and Latin American cuisines. When dietary westernization depletes these populations, the metabolic detoxification chain they supported breaks down. This explains why body odor and breath issues that weren't present in your home country — or in your parents — appear after dietary shift.</p>"
          }
        },
